      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Opponents often raise concerns about meritocracy, arguing that DEI initiatives can favor group identity over individual achievement, which they see as unfair. A common critique is that affirmative action can lead to reverse discrimination, suggesting that it unfairly disadvantages qualified individuals from non-target groups. Furthermore, some argue that focusing on group characteristics overlooks individual merit and competence in hiring or advancement. Being prepared to address these philosophical concerns will help you anticipate and structure strong counterpoints for the workshop.",
