      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. some of the managers are saying that meritocracy isn't just a \"philosophical\" thing but a practical one. they're arguing that if you prioritize diversity metrics, you're essentially lowering the bar and compromising on actual skill or intelligence to hit a quota. they want to know if it's even possible to maintain high performance standards when race becomes a factor in hiring. can you help me flesh out that specific argument? how would someone argue that race-based hiring inherently impacts the quality of the workforce?",
