      "content": "The argument here centers on the idea that if hiring criteria shift from objective performance indicators to demographic targets, the focus on measurable results becomes secondary. Proponents of this view assert that a quota system inherently forces a reduction in standards when candidates must be selected to meet a predetermined statistical goal. This line of reasoning contends that imposing racial criteria introduces bias into performance assessment, ultimately compromising the overall competency level of the workforce. They maintain that genuine high performance requires blind assessment of skills, not demographic balancing.",
